The paper deals with knowledge base inference, which is a topic that falls under artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also proposes and evaluates matrix factorization and tensor factorization models, which are popular machine learning techniques used in various fields such as natural language processing (cs.CL), information retrieval (cs.IR), and database systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the performance of these models on different datasets, which is a common topic in machine learning research (cs.LG).
